Great dish! I altered it a little, but the butternut squash was a great touch. I used ground turkey instead of sausage, and cooked it with habanero and green chile peppers to spice it up. I also added anaheim peppers to the chili to add a little more color and flavor. I used Frontera's Tomatillo Salsa, and that worked wonderfully. I added a bit of water because it was really thick, and I like a little juice in my chili! I served it with a little sour cream and crispy tortilla strips and everyone loved it!

