Rating: 3
Easy one-pot meal--great for a weeknight. I doubled the recipe as one reviewer suggested because I wanted an additional day of leftovers. The recipe as it is written, however, makes MORE than enough. Now I have leftovers for a week--far too much for two people! The dish itself is flavorful and has a nice spice level, although the butternut squash adds a rather incongruous flavor that doesn't combine well with the tomatillo sauce. My husband, who is Mexican and usually picky about any variation on Mexican dishes, did like the dish, but carefully ate around the squash pieces. Next time, I'll substitute potatoes for the butternut squash or perhaps just leave it out. I served it more like a pozole, topped with chopped onions, cilantro, and avocado, along with warm corn tortillas.

